    "narrative": "The lineup construction for April 10th focuses heavily on aggressive exploitation of middle-of-the-road starters and favorable park factors. **Daulton Varsho** (72.16) and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (71.61) headline the slate, with **Varsho** benefiting from a high-upside matchup against Woods Richardson and an elevated spot in the order. **Matt Chapman** (70.11) and **Will Smith** (69.98) also present elite efficiency scores, aided significantly by the park factor at play and favorable wind conditions for **Will Smith**. We are particularly focused on the speed-heavy profiles of **Tyler Freeman** (69.05) and **Jung Hoo Lee** (63.09); both face hurlers with slow deliveries, creating high-percentage opportunities to steal bases\u2014a category we are aggressively hunting given its scarcity.\n\nThe most difficult exclusion today was **Brendan Donovan** (59.16), who fell just shy of the threshold to displace the lower-scoring **Jeremiah Jackson**. While **Brendan Donovan** offers strong platoon advantages, the optimizer favored the sheer park-driven upside of **Jeremiah Jackson** and the lineup security provided by our primary starters. We remain cautious regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Cal Raleigh**, **Will Smith**, **Tyler Freeman**, and **Lawrence Butler**; while our projections assume their standard order placement, any significant drop in the batting order would necessitate a downward revision in their efficiency scores. **Cal Raleigh** (60.97) remains a start, but his score is suppressed by a negative park factor and platoon disadvantage, necessitating a close watch as official lineups circulate.",
